## Testando Métodos Privados de Traits

Use quando o método é `private` ou instancia SDKs com `new`.

### Por Que Não Podemos Mockar Diretamente?

```php
trait GoogleProjectAuthClient
{
    // ❌ Método PRIVADO - não pode ser mockado com getMockBuilder
    private function getGoogleAdsClientBy(string $adsCustomerId, string $refreshToken): GoogleAdsClient
    {
        return (new GoogleAdsClientBuilder())  // ← Chamada real ao Google
            ->withOAuth2Credential($this->getOAuth2Credential($adsCustomerId, $refreshToken))
            ->build();
    }
}
```

### ✅ Solução: Mockar a Estrutura Interna

```php
/**
 * Helper: Mocka a estrutura interna da trait GoogleProjectAuthClient.
 */
private function mockGoogleAdsClientByStructure(GoogleAdsClient $mockGoogleAdsClient): void
{
    // Mock do OAuth2Credential
    $mockOAuth2Credential = Mockery::mock(\Google\Auth\FetchAuthTokenInterface::class);
    
    // Mock do OAuth2TokenBuilder com overload
    $mockOAuth2Builder = Mockery::mock('overload:' . \Google\Ads\GoogleAds\Lib\OAuth2TokenBuilder::class);
    $mockOAuth2Builder->shouldReceive('from')->andReturnSelf();
    $mockOAuth2Builder->shouldReceive('build')->andReturn($mockOAuth2Credential);

    // Mock do GoogleAdsClientBuilder com overload
    $mockBuilder = Mockery::mock('overload:' . \Google\Ads\GoogleAds\Lib\V20\GoogleAdsClientBuilder::class);
    $mockBuilder->shouldReceive('withOAuth2Credential')->andReturnSelf();
    $mockBuilder->shouldReceive('from')->andReturnSelf();
    $mockBuilder->shouldReceive('withTransport')->andReturnSelf();
    $mockBuilder->shouldReceive('build')->andReturn($mockGoogleAdsClient);
}
```

### Usar o Helper no Teste

```php
public function test_unlinkAccountAds_function_and_returns_success()
{
    // Arrange
    $accountEntity = new AccountEntity([
        'id'          => 1,
        'account_ads' => [
            'customer_id'     => '1234567890',
            'manager_link_id' => 'manager_link_123'
        ]
    ]);

    $mockGoogleAdsClient          = Mockery::mock(GoogleAdsClient::class);
    $mockManagerLinkServiceClient = Mockery::mock(CustomerManagerLinkServiceClient::class);

    $mockGoogleAdsClient->shouldReceive('getCustomerManagerLinkServiceClient')
        ->once()
        ->andReturn($mockManagerLinkServiceClient);

    $mockManagerLinkServiceClient->shouldReceive('mutateCustomerManagerLink')
        ->once()
        ->andReturn(Mockery::mock(MutateCustomerManagerLinkResponse::class));

    // ⭐ USAR O HELPER
    $this->mockGoogleAdsClientByStructure($mockGoogleAdsClient);

    GoogleClientService::partialMock()
        ->shouldReceive('getUserAuthData')
        ->once()
        ->andReturn(['refresh_token' => 'mock_token']);

    ApiLog::shouldReceive('info')->once();

    $mockService = $this->getMockBuilder(GoogleAdsConnectService::class)
        ->onlyMethods(['getAccount'])
        ->getMock();

    $mockService->expects($this->once())
        ->method('getAccount')
        ->willReturn($accountEntity);

    // Act
    $mockService->unlinkAccountAds();

    // Assert
    $this->assertTrue(true);
}
```

